<H3> <TI>   HSS Executive Committee Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20573A Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 21 Mar 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20573A </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by nma: "HSS Without Executive Committee"] </F>
  [Text] Zagreb -- According to a public announcement made 
by Dr. Josip Stojanovic, the following members of the HSS 
[Croatian Peasant Party] Executive Committee -- Prof. Dr. 
Ivan Basic, Prof. Ivan Medved, Stanislav Tomcik, Prof. Rudolf 
Zamuda, and Zeljko Pasaric -- have resigned because of 
"dissatisfaction with the leadership of Drago Stipac and the 
decision of the Main Committee to suspend Mirko Madjor and Dr. 
Josip Stojanovic." 
  According to the announcement, "the HSS is left without an 
Executive Committee because the majority of its members have 
resigned." The suspended members of the Party Presidency, Mirko 
Madjor and Josip Stojanovic, will address some public meetings 
organized by the HSS field branches in Slavonia. 

</TEXT>

